## Summary

### PatternFly 6 Migration — Build Fix Complete ✅

**Build command:** `yarn build` (via webpack with fork-ts-checker)
**Result:** 0 errors, 3 pre-existing warnings

### Package upgrades applied in `package.json`:
| Package | Before (PF5) | After (PF6) |
|---------|-------------|-------------|
| `@patternfly/patternfly` | `^5.4.0` | `^6.5.2` |
| `@patternfly/react-charts` | `^7.4.0` | `^8.5.1` |
| `@patternfly/react-core` | `^5.4.0` | `^6.5.1` |
| `@patternfly/react-icons` | `^5.4.0` | `^6.5.1` |
| `@patternfly/react-table` | `^5.4.0` | `^6.5.1` |
| `@patternfly/react-topology` | `^5.4.1` | `^6.5.0` |

**New peer dependencies added:** 17 `victory-*` packages (required by `@patternfly/react-charts` v8).

### Errors fixed (147 total, grouped into 6 categories):

1. **`@patternfly/react-charts` import path** (8 files) — Changed `from '@patternfly/react-charts'` → `from '@patternfly/react-charts/victory'` (v8 moved charts to a subpath).

2. **`Tooltip appendTo="inline"` removed** (42 occurrences across ~25 files) — PF6 `Tooltip` no longer accepts `"inline"` string for `appendTo`. Removed the prop entirely (defaults to `document.body`).

3. **`Switch labelOff` prop removed** (16 occurrences across 12 files) — PF6 `Switch` no longer has `labelOff`. Removed the prop since all values were just `' '`.

4. **`Modal` API restructured** (6 files) — PF6 `Modal` no longer has `actions`, `title`, `header`, `footer` props. Converted to use `<ModalHeader>`, `<ModalBody>`, `<ModalFooter>` child components.

5. **`Button isActive` prop removed** (4 occurrences in 2 files) — PF6 `Button` no longer has `isActive`. Replaced with `aria-pressed`.

6. **`Page` API changes** (1 file) — `header` → `masthead`, `onPageResize` removed. Replaced with a `useEffect` + `window.addEventListener('resize', ...)` to preserve mobile viewport detection.

### Tests
No unit test runner is configured in this project (`jest` is not a dependency and there is no `test` script). Only Cypress e2e tests exist, which require a running OpenShift Console + cluster. Lint passes cleanly.
